Today, @RepBrianMast & I introduced a bipartisan bill that would change the VA's motto to make it more inclusive of women veterans.

The brave women who have worn our nation's uniform deserve to be equally embraced by the agency meant to support them.  https://bit.ly/2PBR4nm

As we marked 100 years since the end of WWI, I laid a wreath at the gravesite of New York native Nurse Alice Hagadorn in Suresnes, France. She served bravely on the front lines during the war. Thank you to Nurse Hagadorn and to all of our veterans for their service & sacrifice. pic.twitter.com/bj8fwH1Uwd
Today we honor the men and women who have served and sacrificed for our country, and we renew our commitment to supporting all veterans and their families – every day. #VeteransDay

The brave women who serve our country deserve to be a part of an organization that fully recognizes their service & sacrifice.

Next week, @SenGillibrand and I will introduce a bill to amend the VA's motto to make it more inclusive of women veterans. https://bit.ly/2PKngUO
